Description:
The business analyst works either independently or as part of a larger team to conduct a variety of quantitative analyses as required to accomplish client mission objectives. A strong foundational knowledge in statistical analysis, research, and identification of causal factors is a strong plus. Analysis may span a broad spectrum to include financial, labor force (census), workforce population, project variances, earned value, etc. The business analyst is expected to be able to interpret guidance and identify the most effective way to gather, analysis, and report information and data to promote business decision making.
Efforts may include document authoring, where quantitative analysis is a major component and or facilitation of business process definition activities aimed at capturing processes and identifying areas of improvement. Strong presentation skills both in development of executive level presentations and or support crafting communications strategies is also needed to be successful in this role.
Primary Duties:
Acts as a liaison between client departments and the project team by:
Opening and maintaining lines of communication with key stakeholders to monitor and improve business services, performance and operations;
Serves as a primary point of contact for departments, offices, and the project team to promote understanding and operational cohesion;
Makes recommendations for product or service enhancements;
Supports ideas and recommendations with sound data analysis;
Supports application of relevant federal regulations into operating streams and associated work functions;
Conducts Congressional, regulatory and legal analysis;
Conducts analysis of detention data services and systems reporting inaccuracies and making recommendations for improvements;
Authors documents, specifications, presentations as required in support of client operations;
Participates in business process modeling sessions, acting as a documentarian, co-facilitator, facilitator, or subject matter expert in sketch sessions;
Conducts interviews and performs analysis in order to create business cases for projects;
Conducts preliminary requirements analysis for project requests, reviews requirements, specifications, conducts tests, provides support and develops training plans;
May act as a project manager on some projects or tasks;
Coordinates activities with Immigration and Custom Enforcement (ICE), Bureau of Prisons (BOP), and other associated client executives and field personnel

